While the feeder is delivering the expected results there is a scope for improvement Following are the areas of improvement:
i.	Weight of the food to be dispensed: The feeder should be enabled with sensor to ensure that the same quantity of food as stated by the shelter staff gets dispensed every time. The quantity can be measured in terms of weight of the food. 
ii.	Alarm on the feeder: in case of any discrepancy such as inadequate quantity of food in the food bin, the feeder should ring an alarm so that staff can be alerted of the issue. 
iii.	Safety measures for pets: The tray should be made of food grade plastic and the tray should be designed in a way that when the pet nibbles on the tray, there are no sharp items to hurt the pet
